'''Al-Nahyan Stadium''' ({{Lang-ar|ملعب آل نهيان}}) is a [[multi-purpose stadium]] in [[Abu Dhabi]], [[United Arab Emirates]].
It is currently used mostly for [[football (soccer)|football]] matches and is the home ground of [[Al-Wahda Club (Abu Dhabi)|Al Wahda]].<ref>{{cite web|title=About Al Wahda Club Facilities|url=http://www.alwahda-fc.com/en/Wahda-Club/Facilities|website=www.alwahda-fc.com|accessdate=3 August 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160723085618/http://www.alwahda-fc.com/en/Wahda-Club/Facilities|archive-date=2016-07-23|dead-url=yes|df=}}</ref> The stadium holds 12,000<ref>{{cite web|url=http://uae.agleague.ae/en/club/al-wahda.html|title=Al Wahda - Clubs - UAE Pro League Committee|publisher=Al Wahda Club}}</ref> people and was built in 1995. The stadium also hosted group games of the [[2003 FIFA World Youth Championship]].
The stadium is being upgraded in preparation for the [[2019 AFC Asian Cup]].
