'''Tenpin bowling''' is a popular and recreational sport in '''India'''. The activity is administered by the [[Bangalore|Banglore]]-based [[Tenpin Bowling Federation of India]].<ref>{{cite news|author=Shrivathsa Sridhar |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-12-05/bangalore/30477213_1_gold-medals-kannan-prathima-hegde |title=Tenpin bowling is right up her alley - Times Of India |publisher=Articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com |date=2011-12-05 |accessdate=2012-07-09}}</ref> It organises the National Bowling League comprising championships for amateurs, corporate team tournaments as well as a national tour for professionals. Many Indians take up [[tenpin bowling|bowling]] for fitness, rather than for recreation.<ref>{{cite web|author=Business Standard |url=http://www.business-standard.com/india/news/bowled-over/443565/ |title=Bowled over |publisher=Business-standard.com |date=2011-07-23 |accessdate=2012-07-09}}</ref> Bowling alleys in [[India]] are commonly a part of multiplexes and malls.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ten-pinbowling.com/setupcenter.html |title=Set up a Ten-Pin Bowling Center! Start enjoying game & money! |publisher=Ten-pinbowling.com |date= |accessdate=2012-07-09}}</ref>
In 2008, the Indian team participated in the [[WTBA World Tenpin Bowling Championships]] in [[Bangkok]]<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.hindu.com/2008/08/19/stories/2008081960602100.htm | location=Chennai, India | work=The Hindu | title=Six-member Indian tenpin bowling team named | date=2008-08-19}}</ref> and the [[Commonwealth Tenpin Bowling Championships]] in [[Belfast]].<ref>http://www.bowlingdigital.com/bowl/node/4869</ref>
Mr. Rajmohan Palaniappan, first Indian to score a perfect game (300) in 40th Singapore Open in the Year 2007 ...
