{{Infobox stadium | name = MKO Abiola Stadium | fullname = MKO Abiola Stadium | former_names = | location = [[Abeokuta]] | built = | opened = | renovated = | expanded = | closed = | owner = | surface = Grass | capacity = 35,000 | record_attendance = | tenants = [[Gateway United F.C.|Gateway United]] }}
'''MKO Abiola Stadium''' is a multi-use [[stadium]] in [[Abeokuta]], [[Nigeria]]. It is currently used mostly for [[football (soccer)|football]] matches and is the home stadium of [[Gateway F.C.]]. The stadium has a capacity of 35,000 people.
==Name== The stadium name refere to [[Moshood Abiola|Moshood Kashimawo Olawale Abiola]] an important businessman, publisher, politician and aristocrat of Abeokuta.
