{{Multiple issues| {{Refimprove|date=October 2017}} {{No footnotes|date=October 2017}}}} {{wiktionary}} '''Roller sports''' are sports that use human powered vehicles which use rolling either by gravity or various pushing techniques. Typically [[ball bearings]] and [[Aggressive inline skating#Wheels|polyurethane wheels]] are used for momentum and traction respectively, and attached to devices or vehicles that the roller puts his weight on. The international governing body is the [[International Roller Sports Federation]] (FIRS).
